<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8">
        <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
        <!-- The above 3 meta tags *must* come first in the head; any other head content must come *after* these tags -->
        <meta name="description" content="">
        <meta name="author" content="">


        <title>Image Annotator</title>

        <!-- Bootstrap core CSS -->
        <link href="/static/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
        <link href="/static/sticky-footer-navbar.css" rel="stylesheet">
        <link href="/static/pace.css" rel="stylesheet">
        <link href="/static/custom.css" rel="stylesheet">

    </head>

    <body>

        <div class="container">

            <div class="page-header">
                <h1>Textual Annotations</h1>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-12">
                    <p><a href="/">Go Home</a></p>
                    <strong>Instructions:</strong>
                    <ol>
                        <li>You will be presented with an image.</li>
                        <li>The images were shot with a personal lifelog camera, i.e. a camera hanging off the chest of the person wearing it. The images depict scenes of everyday life.</li>
                        <li>We ask you to describe each image with as many details as possible. Write your description as if you were the person wearing the camera. For example, write "I am discussing some results with a colleague on a computer monitor in my office.". Include as many details as possible in your description. If an image doesn't have anything in it (for example it is very blurry), then please leave the input field blank and move onto the next image.</li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div id="lifelog-app">

                <section id="main">
                    <strong id="session-annotated"></strong>
                    <div id="lifelog-image-list"></div>
                </section>

            </div>
        </div> <!-- /container -->

        <script src="/static/jquery-1.11.3.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="/static/underscore-min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="/static/backbone-min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="/static/pace.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
        <script src="/static/annotation-textual.js" type="text/javascript"></script>

        <script type="text/template" id="item-template">
            <div id="item-<%- id %>">
                <h3><%- name %></h3>

                <div class="row">

                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <img src="data:image/jpg;base64,<%- data %>" class="img-responsive" />
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                        <p>Provide a description of the image; write it as if you were the person wearing the camera and give as many details as possible.</p>
                        <textarea class="form-control annotation" id="<%- id %>" style="width:100%" rows="10" placeholder="Enter description here." title="Description"></textarea>
                        <button class="btn btn-default save">Next</button>
                    </div>


                </div>
                <hr>
            </div>

        </script>
    </body>
</html>